# Dual GitHub remotes

This project uses **two GitHub repositories** for the same codebase:

| Remote | Repository | Purpose |
|--------|------------|---------|
| `origin` | `Syantw/aqua-map-keeper` | **Primary** — Vercel production/preview deploy |
| `lovable` | `Syantw/aqua-map-keeper-6c6db772` | Lovable editor sync / backend preview |

## Agent workflow

After commits the user approves, **always push to both remotes** on the current branch (default: `syantw/ui-polish-mapbox-loc`):

```bash
npm run push:all
# or: git push origin HEAD && git push lovable HEAD
```

- Treat `origin` as source of truth for deployment.
- Keep `lovable` in sync so Lovable preview matches Vercel.
- Only force-push to `lovable` when the user explicitly asks to overwrite Lovable’s cloud copy.

## Remotes

- Do not remove or rename `origin` / `lovable` without user confirmation.
- Vercel env vars and Supabase Auth stay on the **original** project; Lovable repo is for code sync only unless the user says otherwise.
- **AI label scan** uses Vercel `/api/scan-fixture-label` + `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` on Vercel — do not rely on Lovable Cloud Edge Functions or Lovable AI chat for backend deploy.
